{
  "stem": "13623.5",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I would not eat it right away.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We're march-- they're marching us, which was a familiar sight to us by now, to the same wagons that we came to Auschwitz that we just not too long ago unloaded, the Auschwitz evacuees that came into Dora.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We got into-- into this-- into this cattle train-- train cars.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Some cars-- they didn't have enough cars, some cars were the closed type that we used to come in, and some cars were the open type of cars that is used for-- to carry different merchandise other than humans.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The people that were on the inside in the closed cars, which I was lucky enough to be in one, were so-called the lucky ones.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The people that work in the open cars were-- were loaded to the point not-- you could not sit.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "You had to stand and start from the end of the car and stand, one body against the other, until the car filled up.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Everybody had to stand up.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "The train is going now a day, two, three.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "As the train is-- as the train is moving, especially in the open trains, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] people were so crowded and-- and so uncomfortable that a lot of prisoners, and there was a mixture, you didn't know-- not that you didn't know, you-- there were Jewish prisoners, Polish, Ukrainians, Germans.",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "You could see by-- by-- by their emblems.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Some of the prisoners, in order to get a little more comfortable, it was a matter of the stronger surviving.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Again, it was a survival of the fittest.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They would pick the weaker, throw them overboard as the train was going to wherever we went to, so they should have a little more room.",
      "word_count": 26
    }
  ],
